<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-565-062  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 565 062.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  August 25 1989 n1250* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM perfects circuits need for 100M-byte fibre optic channels.andO;(also introduces Terminal Server)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (innovations).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   IBM Performance 4000-T Terminal Server (Computer communicationsequipment) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     File ServersCommunications EquipmentFiber OpticsOver 19,200 BpsExperimental ComputersGallium Arsenide SemiconductorsNew TechniqueSemiconductor Preparation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM PERFECTS CIRCUITS NEEDED FOR 100M-BYTEandM;FIBRE OPTIC CHANNELSandM;In a development that brings closer superfast channels for its mainframes andthe ability to run physically dispersed systems in single image, IBM reportsthat its scientists have demonstrated two experimental chips for transmittingand receiving data over fibre optic lines at speeds of 1G-bits per second -that's 125M- bits per second, the sort of speed that IBM has been talkingabout for future channels.andP;  The designers believe that the receiver chip isthe densest optoelectronic chip ever reported.andP;  The receiver holds 8,000transistors in geometries down to 1 micron, which is 50 times more opticaland electronic components than ever previously assembled on an optoelectronicchip, IBM claims.andP;  The parts are fabricated in Gallium Arsenide and integrateoptical, data transmission and data conditioning functions in single chips.andO;A GaAs injection laser array that uses quantum well technology is used tocreate the light pulses.andP;  Such quantum-well devices make use of the unusualbehaviour of electrons confined in extremely thin semiconductor layers togenerate light pulses efficiently.andP;  launch of the Performance 4000-T TerminalServer.andP;  Based on the firm's server for DEC local area network users, theproduct supports the TCP/IP transport protocol and enables up to 32 terminalsplus a parallel printer to be connected to an Ethernetwork.andP;  The throughputrate is claimed to translate to handling 16 lines simultaneously at 38.4Kbpsor 32 lines simultaneously at 19.2Kbps.andP;  No word on the processor, but the16-port configuration is $3,900, a 16-port expansion unit is $2,185.andP;  Shipsare planned to begin in September.andO;</TEXT></DOC>